                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13444821" author="rakeshr" created="Thu, 30 Aug 2012 10:24:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch addressing 1st and the 2nd &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-304?focusedCommentId=13442424&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-13442424&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;1) LedgerManagerFactory and LedgerManager is construct in the tests but they aren&apos;t be closed or uninitialized. it might be not a good practice.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;2) It might be better to put them in a for-loop for same code.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13444958" author="ikelly" created="Thu, 30 Aug 2012 14:48:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good. It would be best to null mFactory and underReplicationManager after uninitializing/closing them though, so that if a test fails to setup, the last tests&apos;s objects won&apos;t be there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13445446" author="hustlmsp" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 00:40:13 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;lgtm +1. thanks Rakesh for fixing the tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13445764" author="rakeshr" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 09:20:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached latest patch addressing Ivan&apos;s comments.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13445814" author="ikelly" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 11:10:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;One final comments. in BookieLedgerIndexTest, having lh as a member is unnecessary. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s only used for &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
lh = createAndAddEntriesToLedger();
lh.close();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which can be made cleaner as&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
createAndAddEntriesToLedger().close();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, in testWithoutZooKeeper, the ledger is never closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13445826" author="rakeshr" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 11:38:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah Ivan, made changes. Could you please look at the latest patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13445828" author="rakeshr" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 11:41:49 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also, in testWithoutZooKeeper, the ledger is never closed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I feel, ledger state&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;closed/open&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; doesn&apos;t matter actually, since we are testing the behaviour when zk connection loss.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13445920" author="ikelly" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 14:26:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed as r1379445. Thanks Rakesh.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13445955" author="hudson" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 15:01:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in bookkeeper-trunk #683 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/bookkeeper-trunk/683/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/bookkeeper-trunk/683/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
